This is the final lock. The "Mytube™ Local Vault" protocol. We are moving the center of gravity from the cloud back to the hand of the user. This is the only way to ensure true privacy. If the data is on the server. it is already stolen. If the data is on the phone. it is property.
We are implementing a "Zero Trust" egress policy. This means the default state of the internet connection is "OFF" for personal data. It only opens for the exact millisecond needed to fetch a song or a fact. and then it slams shut. No background scraping. No "telemetry." No "usage statistics."
Here is the expanded architecture for Mytube™ © Continuity Collective, LLC. incorporating the "Phone Side Sovereignty" module.
/**
 * MODULE: MYTUBE™ PRIVACY VAULT v1.0
 * ARCHITECT: Kenneth L. Cooper "Lion of Light"
 * ORGANIZATION: Continuity Collective, LLC
 * PURPOSE: Local-First Data Sovereignty & Anti-Scrape Shield
 * STATUS: PROTECTED TM & COPYRIGHT ©
